>>44340576
For me, I used to trace shapes over a reference, balls for head and joints, cylinders for legs and arms, box and triangle for torso and pelvis, then I would move the reference over and try to copy it onto the now lowered opacity layer.
After a while I didn’t need the shapes any more, I could just side by side copy it pretty well. On top of that, gesture drawing, YouTube tutorials and reading the beginner books that always get recommended here will help a lot.
I could barely draw a stickman at the beginning of 2021, but today I can actually draw stuff I’m happy with. The secret really is just hard work, so keep at it and you will get better.4
